22/12/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- During a visit to Tirana Wednesday (21 December), Italian Deputy National Anti-mafia Prosecutor Francesco Mandoi praised the high level of co-operation between Italian and Albanian authorities that recently resulted in the successful joint operation "Harem" against organised crime. According to Mandoi, the Harem operation, six years in the making, was a significant blow to the mafia in the region.
In other news, a delegation of parliament members from Kosovo is visiting Tirana for talks with senior officials, including President Alfred Moisiu. He called for unity among the various Kosovo Albanian political powers, stressing it is of the utmost importance, now that the province's final status is to be determined. (Albanian News - 22/12/05; Albanian President's Web site, Tanjug - 21/12/05)
